ck\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 21, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104tmu1665702674950.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tmu1665702674950.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tmu1665702674950.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"tmu1665702674950\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"tmu1665702674950___widgets__469777\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The [WIDGETS] section of the assignment file specifies logical to physical widget\n      mappings for character mode. Default mappings are provided in the file\n         <span class=\"ph filepath\">usyschr.asn</span>.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"tmu1665702674950__note_N10023_N1001A_N10001\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> For Windows widget mappings, use the [widgets] section of the initialization file.</div>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"tmu1665702674950__topic_d144227e1_d144228e1_d144229e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1029287e58\">Syntax</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tmu1665702674950__p_d144233e1_d144234e1_d144235e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">LogicalName</var> {<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>}\n               <var class=\"keyword varname\">PhysicalName</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tmu1665702674950__topic_d103307e1_d103308e1_d103309e1_d103310e1_d103311e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1029287e75\">Arguments</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tmu1665702674950__li_d50339e1_d50340e1_d50341e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">LogicalName</var> is the logical\n               widget name as used in Uniface. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tmu1665702674950__li_d50342e1_d50343e1_d50344e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">PhysicalName</var> is the name of\n               the physical widget. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tmu1665702674950__topic_d103312e1_d103313e1_d103314e1_d103315e1_d103316e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1029287e94\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tmu1665702674950__p_d144242e1_d144243e1_d144244e1\">The following example assignment file maps logical widgets to physical widgets as they are defined in the file <span class=\"ph filepath\">usyschr.asn</span>:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[WIDGETS]\nEditBox=ueditbox\nCheckBox=ucheckbox\nRadioGroup=uradiogroup\nDropDownList=udropdownlist\nListBox=ulistbox\nCommandButton=ucmdbutton\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">The following example assignment file includes the file\n               <span class=\"ph filepath\">usyschr.asn</span>:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"tmu1665702674950__pre_qtz_tbn_lwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">; Some assignment file\n#file usysadm:usyschr.asn\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xrd1707815497645.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Assignments</a><p>In ProcScript, the equal sign (=) assigns the result of an expression to a variable, parameter, field, or status function.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yeu1719685518358.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Assignment Settings</a><p>An assignment setting is a setting or definition in an assignment file that determines one aspect of the behavior or environment of a Uniface application. Assignment settings can specify the location of application resources and servers, set environment variables, define application logicals, and set Uniface system settings to influence runtime behavior.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532427\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532427\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "[WIDGETS] Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 The [WIDGETS] section of the assignment file specifies logical to physical widget mappings for character mode. Default mappings are provided in the file usyschr.asn . Note: For Windows widget mappings, use the [widgets] section of the initialization file. Syntax LogicalName { = } PhysicalName Arguments LogicalName is the logical widget name as used in Uniface. PhysicalName is the name of the physical widget. Description The following example assignment file maps logical widgets to physical widgets as they are defined in the file usyschr.asn : [WIDGETS] EditBox=ueditbox CheckBox=ucheckbox RadioGroup=uradiogroup DropDownList=udropdownlist ListBox=ulistbox CommandButton=ucmdbutton Copy The following example assignment file includes the file usyschr.asn : ; Some assignment file #file usysadm:usyschr.asn Copy Related Links Assignments In ProcScript, the equal sign (=) assigns the result of an expression to a variable, parameter, field, or status function. Assignment Settings An assignment setting is a setting or definition in an assignment file that determines one aspect of the behavior or environment of a Uniface application. Assignment settings can specify the location of application resources and servers, set environment variables, define application logicals, and set Uniface system settings to influence runtime behavior. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}